parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the 360 surround view camera system can cause reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially when reversing or parking.
symptoms: Cameras not working
intermittent camera failure
front or rear cameras not functioning
or both.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain issue can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks, especially at night or in remote areas.
symptoms: Battery dies after 48 hours of inactivity
repeated jumpstarts
sporadic issues with unlocking and locking car doors via hand touch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the trunk while the vehicle is in motion can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Trunk pops open on its own while the vehicle is in motion
with no warning lamps or messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the tow system can cause unsafe towing conditions, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Tow system does not work properly
no communication with the brake controller
incorrect wiring of the brakes
and shock when plugging in a tester to the 7-way connector.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable downshifting and lurching forward of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially in stop-and-go traffic, as it makes it difficult for the driver to gauge when the car will come to a complete stop. This can lead to rear-end collisions or other accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches or surges forward when downshifting
especially when approaching a complete stop
making it difficult to control the vehicle's movement. This can occur in various drive modes
with or without Autostart/stop engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Gas Pedal Sticking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the gas pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to a loss of vehicle control, increased speed, and potential accidents, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal feels stuck or stuck to the floor
the vehicle continues to accelerate even after the foot is removed from the pedal
the vehicle slows down when the brake is applied but accelerates again when the brake is released
the vehicle's speed increases rapidly and uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Backup Camera and Surround View System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera and surround view system can increase the risk of "back over" accidents, particularly involving young children, which can result in serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The backup camera and surround view system fail to function
displaying a blank or distorted image
or not turning on at all
making it difficult for the driver to see objects or people behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair and Maintenance of Backup Camera and Surround View System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability of authorized service centers to repair the backup camera and surround view system can lead to prolonged periods of vehicle downtime, causing inconvenience and potential safety risks to the driver and others.
symptoms: The vehicle is repeatedly returned to the authorized service center for repairs
with the issue persisting despite multiple attempts to fix it
resulting in extended periods of vehicle downtime.
